<header>
	
		
		Which of the following do you think would be good advice to a candidate about to do IELTS Speaking Part 2? Click yes or no against the statements.
		
</header>
	
<section id="body">
  <img class="rightFloat" src="../media/MM_SP_003.jpg" mode="1" id="1001"/>
  <br/>
  <ol id="questionList">
    <br/>
    <li id="q1">Talk confidently.  <a id="a1">Yes</a><tab/><a id="a2">No</a><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q2">Feel free to correct yourself if you make a mistake. <a id="a3">Yes</a><tab/><a id="a4">No</a><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q3">Tell the examiner you are very nervous. <a id="a5">Yes</a><tab/><a id="a6">No</a><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q4">Smile and look directly at the examiner. <a id="a7">Yes</a><tab/><a id="a8">No</a><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q5">Think of enough material to talk about until the examiner stops you.<a id="a9">Yes</a><tab/><a id="a10">No</a><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q6">Show interest in the topic.<a id="a11">Yes</a><tab/><a id="a12">No</a><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q7">Learn by heart several short speeches on topics which may come up. <a id="a13">Yes</a><tab/><a id="a14">No</a><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q8">Don't speak about something if you know nothing about it. <a id="a15">Yes</a><tab/><a id="a16">No</a><br/></li>
  </ol>
</section>

<section id="fb1">
  <p align="left">Confidence is a positive thing and will make what you say more interesting.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb2">
  <p align="left">
    <font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">Correcting yourself shows that you are aware of the mistake and that you know the correct language too. This is positive.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb3">
  <p align="left">
    <font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">The examiner expects you to be a bit nervous. There is no need to say it.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb4">
  <p align="left">
    <font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">This is a friendly thing to do and helps establish good communication.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb5">
  <p align="left">
    <font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">In Part 2 it is good to talk until the examiner stops you.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb6">
  <p align="left">
    <font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">If you show interest, then what you say will be more interesting to the examiner.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb7">
  <p align="left">
    <font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">Learning by heart will not help you in this exam. It may cause you to lose marks.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb8">
  <p align="left">
    <font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">You are not expected to know everything, but you should express an opinion or some thoughts on everything you are asked.</font>
  </p>
</section>

